    "rationale": "All 13 V&V 40 credibility factors assessed. Twelve of thirteen factors meet or exceed required levels. The Test conditions factor achieved level 2 against a required level 3; however, the assessment team determined that the single-condition ASTM F1717 protocol is standard industry practice and that the quantitative output comparison results (E/uval < 1.96 for all QoIs) provide sufficient confidence to support an Accepted decision at Medium assurance. The overall credibility evidence is judged consistent with a Medium assurance level for this Class II device application.",
